wikipedia_page.main: Joe Pritchard is a footballer who played for Tranmere Rovers and Ellesmere Port. He scored 29 goals in 178 appearances for Tranmere, before moving to Ellesmere Port in June 1970. He was later employed as a joiner in Cammell Laird shipyard.
